RasterFunctionTemplate.Name: MNDWI Colorized
RasterFunctionTemplate.Description: Modified Normalized Difference Water Index with color map computed as (b3 - b6) / (b3 + b6). Wetlands and moist areas are blues, and dry areas in deep yellow and brown.

Function.Name: Colormap
Function.Description: Changes pixel values to display the raster data as either a grayscale or a red, green, blue (RGB) image, based on a colormap or a color ramp.

Function.Name: Stretch
Function.Description: Enhances an image by adjusting the range of values displayed. This does not alter the underlying pixel values. If a pixel has a value outside of the specified range, it will appear as either the minimum or maximum value.

AnyType.Name: MNDWI Colorized
AnyType.Description: Modified Normalized Difference Moisture Index with color map computed as (b3 - b6) / (b3 + b6). Wetlands and moist areas are blues, and dry areas in deep yellow and brown.

Function.Name: Modified Normalized Difference Water Index
Function.Description: Calculates indexes using predefined formulas or a user-defined expression.
